text.__SUMMARY__:
Acacia everistii is a shrub belonging to the genus Acacia and the subgenus Phyllodineae native to Queensland.
The shrub usually has few branches and typically grows to a height of 3 to 5 m (9.8 to 16.4 ft).It has a scattered distribution from Brovinia in the south east to Expedition Range on the Blackdown Tableland of south eastern Queensland where it grows in sandy or loamy soils over or around sandstone as a part of open Eucalyptus woodland communities.
